HEADWORD: Jacobæan lily
<hw>Jac`o*b⟦ae⟧"an lil"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[See
<er>Jacobean</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A bulbous plant
(<spn>Amaryllis formosissima</spn> syn. <spn>Sprekelia
formosissima</spn>) from Mexico. It bears a single, large, deep, red,
lilylike flower.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Jacobean</asp>.]</altsp></p>

